{
  "metadata": {
    "ep_id": "001",
    "title": "Episode 001",
    "course": "Real Reaction"
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "Intro",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "활기차게",
      "text": "What’s up, world! Welcome to the very first episode of Talkori! I'm your host, John!",
      "translation": "",
      "lang": "EN",
      "audio": "RR_001_s001.mp3",
      "playable": false,
      "seq": 1,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Intro",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "밝게",
      "text": "안녕하세요 여러분!",
      "translation": "Hello everyone!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s002.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 2,
      "insight": {
        "title": "여러분",
        "description": "A polite way to address a group of people, similar to 'Everyone'",
        "usage_tip": "Commonly used by broadcasters or MCs to greet their audience."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Intro",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "미소 지으며",
      "text": "센스쟁이 DJ, 미나입니다!",
      "translation": "I'm Talkori’s witty DJ, Mina!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s003.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 3,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Intro",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "장난스럽게",
      "text": "John. 오늘 텐션이 아주 좋은데요?",
      "translation": "John, your energy is great today!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s004.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 4,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Intro",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "흥분하며",
      "text": "Of course! Mina, you won't believe what happened this morning. I saw a pigeon... waiting for the subway! On the platform!",
      "translation": "",
      "lang": "EN",
      "audio": "RR_001_s005.mp3",
      "playable": false,
      "seq": 5,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Intro",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "크게 웃으며",
      "text": "에이~ 설마요!",
      "translation": "No way!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s006.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 6,
      "insight": {
        "title": "설마요",
        "description": "An expression of disbelief, similar to 'No way' or 'Don't tell me'",
        "usage_tip": "Adding '요' at the end makes it polite."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Intro",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "궁금해하며",
      "text": "비둘기가 지하철을 기다렸다고요?",
      "translation": "A pigeon waiting for the subway?",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s007.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 7,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Intro",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "억울해하며",
      "text": "No, I'm serious! It was standing behind the yellow line!",
      "translation": "",
      "lang": "EN",
      "audio": "RR_001_s008.mp3",
      "playable": false,
      "seq": 8,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Intro",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "장난스럽게",
      "text": "말도 안 돼!",
      "translation": "No way!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s009.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 9,
      "insight": {
        "title": "말도 안 돼",
        "description": "Literally means 'It doesn't even make sense'",
        "usage_tip": "Used for shocking or ridiculous situations that are hard to believe."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Intro",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "웃으며",
      "text": "비둘기가 매너가 너무 좋은 거 아니에요?",
      "translation": "Isn't that pigeon too polite?",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s010.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 10,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Intro",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "웃음",
      "text": "Right? And that's exactly what we're talking about today! Those moments when you just have to say, \"No way!\" or \"Are you serious?\"",
      "translation": "",
      "lang": "EN",
      "audio": "RR_001_s011.mp3",
      "playable": false,
      "seq": 11,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Intro",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "의욕적으로",
      "text": "맞아요.",
      "translation": "Exactly.",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s012.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 12,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Intro",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "설명하며",
      "text": "한국어에는 놀람의 강도나 뉘앙스에 따라 정말 다양한 표현이 있거든요. 오늘 다 파헤쳐 봅시다!",
      "translation": "In Korean, there are so many expressions depending on the intensity or nuance of surprise. Let's dig into them today!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s013.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 13,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "",
      "text": "Okay, Mina. In English, we just say \"No way!\" but in Korea, I hear '진짜?' like... a thousand times a day.",
      "translation": "",
      "lang": "EN",
      "audio": "RR_001_s014.mp3",
      "playable": false,
      "seq": 14,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "공감하며",
      "text": "맞아요.",
      "translation": "Correct.",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s015.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 15,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "미소 지으며",
      "text": "'진짜?'는 거의 한국인의 리액션 기본값이죠.",
      "translation": "'Jinjja?' is pretty much the default reaction for Koreans.",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s016.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 16,
      "insight": {
        "title": "진짜?",
        "description": "The most common way to say 'Really?' or 'For real?'",
        "usage_tip": "Use a rising intonation for a question, and a falling one to confirm a fact."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "",
      "text": "But what if I'm like... 200% surprised? Like the pigeon subway thing?",
      "translation": "",
      "lang": "EN",
      "audio": "RR_001_s017.mp3",
      "playable": false,
      "seq": 17,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "설명하며",
      "text": "그럴 땐 '말도 안 돼!'를 쓰세요.",
      "translation": "In that case, use 'Mal-do an dwae!'",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s018.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 18,
      "insight": {
        "title": "말도 안 돼",
        "description": "Used when something is logically impossible or absurd",
        "usage_tip": "It’s a very natural reaction to hearing something 'crazy'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "따라하며",
      "text": "말도 안 돼!",
      "translation": "No way!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s019.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 19,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "흥미로워하며",
      "text": "Oh, I like the rhythm. What about when I think someone is lying to me? Like a friendly prank?",
      "translation": "",
      "lang": "EN",
      "audio": "RR_001_s020.mp3",
      "playable": false,
      "seq": 20,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "익살스럽게",
      "text": "그럴 땐 손사래를 치면서 이렇게 말해보세요.",
      "translation": "In that case, wave your hand and say it like this.",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s021.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 21,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "연기하며",
      "text": "\"에이~ 거짓말!\"",
      "translation": "\"Ay~ you're lying!\"",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s022.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 22,
      "insight": {
        "title": "에이, 거짓말",
        "description": "'Ay, you're lying' or 'You're joking'",
        "usage_tip": "Used to playfully doubt someone's story."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "따라하듯",
      "text": "에이~ 거짓말!",
      "translation": "Ay, you're lying!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s023.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 23,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "확인하며",
      "text": "It sounds like \"you're lying!\" right?",
      "translation": "",
      "lang": "EN",
      "audio": "RR_001_s024.mp3",
      "playable": false,
      "seq": 24,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "칭찬하며",
      "text": "정확해요!",
      "translation": "Exactly!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s025.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 25,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "보충하며",
      "text": "정말 믿고 싶지 않은 부정적인 놀람일 때는 \"설마...!\"라고 하세요.",
      "translation": "Use \"Seol-ma...!\" for negative disbelief.",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s026.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 26,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "진지하게",
      "text": "그리고 논리적으로 가능성이 없을 땐... \"그럴 리가요!\"...라고 하면 완벽합니다.",
      "translation": "And when something is logically impossible, \"Geureol riga-yo!\" is perfect.",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s027.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 27,
      "insight": {
        "title": "그럴 리가요",
        "description": "'That can't be true' or 'It's impossible'",
        "usage_tip": "Used when you are certain something couldn't have happened based on logic."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "감탄하며",
      "text": "Wow, so many layers! And of course, we can't forget my favorite... 대박!",
      "translation": "",
      "lang": "EN",
      "audio": "RR_001_s028.mp3",
      "playable": false,
      "seq": 28,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "크게 웃으며",
      "text": "당연하죠!",
      "translation": "Of course!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s029.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 29,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Vocab",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "활기차게",
      "text": "'대박'은 그냥 \"Amazing\", \"Crazy\", \"Unbelievable\"... 모두 다 됩니다!",
      "translation": "'Daebak' covers Amazing, Crazy, and Unbelievable!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s030.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 30,
      "insight": {
        "title": "대박",
        "description": "Originally meant 'Huge hit', but now used for any surprising situation",
        "usage_tip": "Works for both very positive and very shocking news."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "",
      "text": "Alright, let's put these into a real situation. Listeners, imagine Mina and I are checking out a famous restaurant in Seoul.",
      "translation": "",
      "lang": "EN",
      "audio": "RR_001_s031.mp3",
      "playable": false,
      "seq": 31,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "들뜬 목소리로",
      "text": "John, 여기 메뉴판 좀 보세요.",
      "translation": "John, look at the menu here.",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s032.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 32,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "놀라운 표정으로",
      "text": "이 식당은 떡볶이 1인분이 5만 원이래요!",
      "translation": "This place says Tteokbokki is 50,000 won per serving!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s033.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 33,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "깜짝 놀라며",
      "text": "What? 진짜요?",
      "translation": "Really?",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s034.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 34,
      "insight": {
        "title": "진짜요?",
        "description": "The polite version of 'Jinjja?'",
        "usage_tip": "Use this with people you aren't close to or in formal settings."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "믿기지 않는듯",
      "text": "떡볶이가 오만 원이라고요?",
      "translation": "Tteokbokki is 50,000 won?",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s035.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 35,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "진지하게",
      "text": "네. 대신 금가루가 뿌려져서 나온대요.",
      "translation": "Yes. But they say it's served with gold dust sprinkled on top.",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s036.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 36,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "어이없다는 듯",
      "text": "말도 안 돼!",
      "translation": "No way!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s037.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 37,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "궁금해하며",
      "text": "금가루요? 설마 진짜 금은 아니겠죠?",
      "translation": "Gold dust? Surely it’s not real gold, right?",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s038.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 38,
      "insight": {
        "title": "설마",
        "description": "Means 'Surely not' or 'No way'",
        "usage_tip": "Often used at the beginning of a sentence to express doubt about a negative possibility."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "천연덕스럽게",
      "text": "진짜 금이래요. 먹으면 건강해진다는 소문이 있어요.",
      "translation": "They say it's real gold. There's a rumor that eating it makes you healthy.",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s039.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 39,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "의심하며",
      "text": "에이, 거짓말!",
      "translation": "Ay, you're lying!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s040.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 40,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "따지듯",
      "text": "미나 씨. 지금 저 속이는 거죠?",
      "translation": "Mina, you're teasing me right now, aren't you?",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s041.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 41,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "결국 웃음을 터뜨리며",
      "text": "하하하! 들켰네요. 사실 5천 원이에요.",
      "translation": "Hahaha! You caught me. Actually, it's 5,000 won.",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s042.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 42,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "안도하며",
      "text": "휴..., 그럼 그렇지!",
      "translation": "Whew, I knew it!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s043.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 43,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "단호하게",
      "text": "그럴 리가 없잖아요!",
      "translation": "There’s no way it could be like that!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s044.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 44,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "장난기 가득하게",
      "text": "근데 제가 다 먹어버려서 John 씨 건 없어요.",
      "translation": "But I ate it all, so there's none left for you, John.",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s045.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 45,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "좌절하며",
      "text": "대박...",
      "translation": "Unbelievable...",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s046.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 46,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Dial",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "슬프게",
      "text": "미나 씨 진짜 너무해요!",
      "translation": "Mina, you're really too much!",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s047.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 47,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Outro",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "웃으며",
      "text": "Wow, that was a roller coaster of emotions!",
      "translation": "",
      "lang": "EN",
      "audio": "RR_001_s048.mp3",
      "playable": false,
      "seq": 48,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Outro",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "활기차게",
      "text": "그쵸?",
      "translation": "Right?",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s049.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 49,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Outro",
      "speaker": "Mina",
      "emotion": "뿌듯하게",
      "text": "이 표현들만 잘 써도 한국 친구들이랑 대화할 때 리액션 장인이 될 수 있어요.",
      "translation": "From 'Jinjja?' to 'Daebak', just by using these expressions, you can become a reaction master when talking with Korean friends.",
      "lang": "KO",
      "audio": "RR_001_s050.mp3",
      "playable": true,
      "seq": 50,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Outro",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "차분하게",
      "text": "Alright, let's wrap up.",
      "translation": "",
      "lang": "EN",
      "audio": "RR_001_s051.mp3",
      "playable": false,
      "seq": 51,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Outro",
      "speaker": "John",
      "emotion": "정리하며",
      "text": "Everyone, remember these five expressions:",
      "translation": "",
      "lang": "EN",
      "audio": "RR_001_s052.mp3",
      "playable": false,
      "seq": 52,
      "insight": null
    },
    {
      "type": "Outro",
